data.description: Give us a second look!!  No carpet in this unit. New flooring upstairs to match downstairs! If you have seen this unit before, it's time to revisit! No carpet in the home! End-unit townhouse in gated Buckhead community has a private courtyard and huge backyard beyond the gate. There is a huge side yard, too. This is the closest thing to a house that you can get! The outdoor space is highlighted by a freshly updated courtyard with pavers, stonework, a custom-built cedar planter chock full of greens! French doors frame the oasis perfectly from inside. This unit was renovated about 3 years ago featuring a beautiful kitchen with granite, white cabinetry & stainless appliances. The glass tile backsplash adds contemporary flair. LVP floor on main level and upstairs. A laundry room with cabinets & a half-bath complete the main level. Upstairs are 2 en-suites with renovated full bathrooms with new vanities, lighting, tilework, fixtures and faucets. One bedroom has nice walk-in closet and the other offers a wall-of-closets. Cross Creek is a gated community in the heart of Buckhead. Resort-style amenities include a par-3, 18-hole golf course with pro-shop, lighted tennis & pickle ball courts, 3 saline pools, 2 clubhouses, a restaurant & bar, gym, pocket parks, Electric Vehicle Charging Stations & recycling station. You are literally a 15 minute drive to the airport, Vinings & more. There are 5 Publix's within 2 miles of Cross Creek. Located in top-rated Morris Brandon Elementary School. Condo fee includes: Water, Sewer & Trash, Roof, Pools, Tennis & Pickleball, Landscaping, Exterior Maintenance, 24/7 Gate Attendant & more! The Upper Westside is a half mile away offering hundreds of shops & eateries including , Henri's, the Work's, Westside Provisions & the breweries: Monday Night Brewery, Bold Monk, Steady Hand and so much more! This property qualifies for a First Time Home Buyer Grant up to $4000.
